    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="[1st Aug-Sep 2020,Borno state]Linked to implied exhaustion of coping strategies, a few KIs directly mentioned coping strategies that they used to apply but were no longer able to. These coping strategies included selling livestock (1), eating stored food (1) or getting support from neighbours or relatives (6). In addition to the KIs describing people in their settlements no longer being able to rely on neighbours or relatives for support, 10 KIs mentioned not being able to get support from neighbours or relatives in general without describing if this had ever been an option. Of those describing getting support from neighbours or relatives in the past some KIs mentioned a decrease in the food available as the reason for this (see quote below)."/>
    <cas:View sofa="1" members="8 19 24 29 34 39 52 65 78 91 104 117 130 143 156 169 182 195 208 221 234 247 260 273 286 299 312 325 338 351 364 377 390 403 416 429 442 455 468 481 494 507 520 533 546 559 572 585 598 611 624 637 650 663 676 689 702 715 728 741 754 767 780 793 806 819 832 845 858 871 884 897 910 923 936 949 962 975 988 1001 1014 1027 1040 1053 1066 1079 1092 1105 1118 1131 1144 1157 1170 1183 1196 1209 1222 1235 1248 1261 1274 1287 1300 1313 1326 1339 1352 1365 1378 1391 1404 1417 1430 1443 1456 1469 1482 1495 1508 1521 1534 1547 1560 1573 1586 1599 1612 1625 1638 1651 1664 1677 1690 1703 1716 1729 1742 1755 1768 1781 1794 1807 1820 1833 1846 1859 1872 1900 1885 1905 1890 1910 1895 1936 1941 1953 1929 1922 1915 1946 1958 1972 1965 1968 1975 1979 1992"/>
